Probably. It's hard to keep technological advances that significant secret for long.
Overall, guns of anthro societies would probably be fairly simplistic with few intricate parts to enable them to not only use but also repair them. Bolt action rifles would likely dominate the scene, with revolvers being the only handguns to speak of and probably also being seen as a sign of wealth and/or marksmanship to own one. Crewed weapons like heavy machineguns would probably still exist, though possibly only as quick-fire semi-automatic weapons instead of full-auto, but be much more primitive than ours and would be the ultimate display of power on an individual scale and would be reserved for the highest priority things to be defended. Double-barreled shotguns would definitely also still exist. If you have a decent knowledge of guns then stick to the really cheap and simplest ones. More parts means more opportunities for fur to get in and jam something up and harder to work with for someone with very poor dexterity.
All of that would only make it easier for someone to attempt to reverse-engineer whatever guns they did find, or even just observe, from this secretive race.
